but I broke the law to get you out.

22
00:00:12,950 --> 00:00:15,620
我是来夸奖你摆脱希拉・赛斯的方式的
I came here to compliment you on getting rid of Sheila Sazs.

23
00:00:15,620 --> 00:00:18,050
如果她在庭审前没有回来
If she's not back by the start of trial,

24
00:00:18,050 --> 00:00:20,510
我会认为你想被起诉
I'm gonna assume you want to be brought up on charges.

25
00:00:20,530 --> 00:00:22,660
我只是过来给你这个限制令
I just stopped by to give you this restraining order

26
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:24,500
阻止你在路易・利特的律师不在场的情况下接触他
preventing you from contacting Louis Litt.

27
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,670
你休想再继续挑拨我和我的人了
You're done driving a wedge between me and my people.

28
00:00:26,670 --> 00:00:29,180
如果我为自己辩护  那我在庭上的每一秒
If I represent myself, every second I'm up there

29
00:00:29,180 --> 00:00:30,340
他们都会看到我就是个律师
they're gonna see me as a lawyer.

30
00:00:30,340 --> 00:00:31,670
但如果她在其中任何一刻
And if she rattles you

31
00:00:31,670 --> 00:00:33,460
打乱你的阵脚
For one of those goddamn seconds,

32
00:00:33,470 --> 00:00:34,660
他们就会认为你是个骗子
they're gonna see you as a fraud

33
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:36,400
并且再也不会看到你的其他方面
and they're never gonna see you as anything else.

34
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:40,410
迈克・罗斯有没有到哈佛大学法学院上过学
Did Mike Ross go to Harvard Law School or not?

35
00:00:40,410 --> 00:00:42,610
我要使用宪法第五修正案赋予我的权利
I'd like to assert my Fifth Amendment right.

36
00:00:43,350 --> 00:00:45,430
如果我在陪审团  我会认定你有罪
If I was on that jury, I'd find you guilty.

37
00:00:45,430 --> 00:00:47,520
他们不会允许我
They're not gonna let me change my goddamn lawyer

38
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:48,510
在庭审过程换律师的
in the middle of a trial.

39
00:00:48,510 --> 00:00:50,190
我们得想办法让他们允许
We need to figure out a way to make them,

40
00:00:50,190 --> 00:00:52,200
因为如果我们想不出  就会输
'cause if we don't, we're gonna lose.

41
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,960
你有最后一个自救的机会
You have one last chance to save yourself.

42
00:00:54,970 --> 00:00:56,840
打电话给我  以免太迟了
Call me before it's too late.

43
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:03,570
好了  我们有一个计划
Okay, so we have a plan for you

44
00:01:03,570 --> 00:01:04,580
可以让你开始为自己辩护
to start representing yourself.

45
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:07,260
还缺个能在执行时乱了吉布斯阵脚的办法
We just need a way to rattle Gibbs when we execute it.

46
00:01:07,260 --> 00:01:08,690
我有个办法  但是
I have a way, but...

47
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:10,270
你不会喜欢的
you're not gonna like it.

48
00:01:12,370 --> 00:01:13,970
我要让克利福德・丹纳出庭作证
I'm gonna call Clifford Danner to the stand.

49
00:01:13,970 --> 00:01:15,320
不行  太冒险了
No way, it's too risky.

50
00:01:15,330 --> 00:01:17,640
-哈维  听我说  -他很愤怒还不稳定
- Harvey, listen to me-- - he's angry and volatile

51
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:19,000
而且我提醒你
and in case you forgot,

52
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,560
你曾经蠢到把你的秘密告诉别人
he's one of the people you were dumb enough

53
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,450
他就是其中之一
to tell your secret to. 

54
00:01:21,450 --> 00:01:22,420
这些我都知道
I know all of that,

55
00:01:22,460 --> 00:01:24,470
但你自己也说  我们需要同情
but you said it yourself, we need sympathy,

56
00:01:24,470 --> 00:01:26,460
没有人比我们从监狱里救出来的无辜之人
and no one is gonna get us more sympathy

57
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:28,160
更能给我们挣到同情了
than the innocent guy we got out of prison.

58
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:30,840
哈维  你说过这件事我必须自己去做
Harvey, you said I needed to do this.

59
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,550
这就是我做事的方式
Well, this is how I do it.

60
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:36,310
你对我有信心吗
Do you have faith in me or not?

61
00:01:46,330 --> 00:01:47,650
格洛丽亚・丹纳夫人吗
Mrs. Gloria Danner?

62
00:01:47,830 --> 00:01:49,990
-是的  -你好  我叫迈克・罗斯
- Yes. - Hi, my name is Mike Ross.

63
00:01:49,990 --> 00:01:51,830
我是皮-斯-利律师事务所的律师  我想
I'm a lawyer at Pearson Specter Litt and I was hoping--

64
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,170
我知道你是谁
I know who you are,

65
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,630
我也知道你来做什么
and I know what you're doing here.

66
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,690
你是来让克利福德出庭为你作证的
You've come to get Clifford to testify for you,

67
00:01:59,510 --> 00:02:01,300
但他恐怕去不了
but I'm afraid he's not going to.

68
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:02,650
拜托了  女士  我保证
Please, ma'am, I promise you,

69
00:02:02,650 --> 00:02:03,890
地检官不能重开他的案子
the D.A. cannot reopen his case--

70
00:02:03,890 --> 00:02:06,300
我不是怕地检官
I'm not talking about the district attorney.

71
00:02:07,690 --> 00:02:10,200
我儿子死了  罗斯先生
My son's dead, Mr. Ross.

72
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:13,050
什么
What?

73
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:16,060
克利福德三周前被枪杀了  所以
Clifford was shot and killed three weeks ago, so...

74
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:19,110
很抱歉  他帮不了你了
I'm sorry, he can't help you.

75
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:23,300
-你好  -你在办公室吗
- Hello? - Are you in the office?

76
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:25,260
现在是周四晚上  我在看我的节目
It's Thursday night. I'm watching my show.

77
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:27,590
录下来晚点看  我需要你帮忙
Well, then goddamn tivo it because I need your help.

78
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:30,320
你用这种语气跟我说话  最好事情很重要
It better be important if you're taking that tone with me.

79
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,180
如果这是麻将馆的事...
And if this is about that mah-jongg game--

80
00:02:32,180 --> 00:02:33,750
我才不在乎什么该死的麻将
I don't give a shit if it's mah-jongg

81
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:35,910
宫爆鸡丁还是跳棋
or kung pao or chinese checkers.

82
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:37,090
这是你这一辈子
This is the most important thing

83
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:39,190
我会让你做的最重要的事
that I'm ever gonna ask you to do in your entire life.

84
00:02:40,230 --> 00:02:41,420
给我下命令吧
Give me an order.

85
00:02:41,540 --> 00:02:43,100
我要你用尽一切办法
I need you to pull whatever strings you have

86
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:44,820
帮我搞到迈克这个案子的庭审记录
to get me a transcript of Mike's trial

87
00:02:44,830 --> 00:02:46,290
并且对此保密
and I need you to keep it to yourself.

88
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:47,740
介意我问一下你要这个做什么吗
Mind if I ask what you need it for?

89
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:50,170
因为我得知道我们有没有一丁点机会
Because I need to know if we have a snowball's chance in hell

90
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,210
打赢这个官司
of winning this thing.

91
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,580
辩方准备好传唤第一位证人了吗
Is defense ready to call its first witness?

92
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:55,750
准备好了  法官大人
I am, Your Honor. 

93
00:02:55,930 --> 00:02:56,580
什么
What?

94
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:57,630
我要传唤证人了
I'm calling my witness.

95
00:02:57,630 --> 00:02:59,340
控方对此有什么疑问吗
Does prosecution have a problem with that?

96
00:02:59,890 --> 00:03:01,970
反对  这太过分了  法官大人
Objection, this is outrageous, Your Honor.

97
00:03:01,970 --> 00:03:03,780
他们不能在庭审中途换律师
They can't switch attorneys in the middle of a trial.

98
00:03:03,780 --> 00:03:05,530
你说得对  但事实上
And that would be true except for the fact

99
00:03:05,530 --> 00:03:07,570
我从一开始就是这个案子的联席律师
that I've been co-counsel on this case from day one.

100
00:03:07,570 --> 00:03:09,430
联席律师  你在说什么
Co-counsel? What planer are you living on?

101
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:11,950
皮-斯-利律师事务所是我的辩护律师
The one where Pearson Specter Litt is my attorney of record.

102
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:13,780
这是员工任务分配书
I have the employee directory right here.

103
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:14,750
里面有我的名字
My name is in it. 

104
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:16,510
此案开审以来就在这里了
It's been there since the beginning of this trial,

105
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,790
你如果想要反对我
and if you wanted to object to me,

106
00:03:17,790 --> 00:03:18,770
应该在开庭的时候
you would have had to have done it

107
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:20,390
就提出反对
at the beginning of this trial.

108
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,300
那我要他们放弃一切申请无效审判的权利
Then I want them waiving all rights to a mistrial

109
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,400
并且记录在案
and I want it in the record. 

110
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,560
法官大人  我不能因为
Your Honor, I'm not gonna be punished 

111
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,630
她不知道我从头到尾
just because she didn't understand

112
00:03:25,630 --> 00:03:27,880
都是自己的辩护律师而受到惩罚
that I've been representing myself this whole time.

113
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,090
他说得有道理  吉布斯女士
He's got a point, Ms. Gibbs.

114
00:03:29,090 --> 00:03:31,160
那基于他为自己辩护的基础上
Then I want them waiving all rights to a mistrial

115
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,970
我要他们放弃一切申请无效审判的权利
based on him representing himself.

116
00:03:32,970 --> 00:03:34,600
乐意之至  法官大人  因为我根本
My pleasure, Your Honor, 'cause I don't expect

117
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,140
不认为我们需要申请无效审判
we'll be needing a mistrial at all.

118
00:03:36,310 --> 00:03:37,660
那就传唤你的第一个证人吧
Then call your first witness.

119
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:40,290
辩方请求传唤格洛丽亚・丹纳出庭作证
Defense would like to call Gloria Danner to the stand.

120
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:43,190
请告诉陪审团你的姓名
Please state your name for the jury.

121
00:03:43,330 --> 00:03:45,110
格洛丽亚・丹纳
Gloria Danner.

122
00:03:45,510 --> 00:03:46,550
丹纳夫人
Mrs. Danner,

123
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,810
数年前  你的儿子克利福德
A number of years ago, your son Clifford

124
00:03:48,810 --> 00:03:51,690
被判谋杀罪入狱
was convicted of murder and sentenced to prison,

125
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,360
-对吗  -是的
- is that right? - Yes.

126
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,120
他是无辜入狱的
For a crime he didn't commit.

127
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,430
如果他被判有罪
How do you know he didn't commit it

128
00:03:56,430 --> 00:03:57,670
你怎么知道他是无辜的呢
if he was convicted of it?

129
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:59,430
因为你证明了他无罪
Because you proved he didn't.

130
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,400
丹纳女士  你能告诉陪审团
Mrs. Danner, can you tell the jury

131
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,630
为什么今天是你出庭作证
why it is that you're here today testifying

132
00:04:03,630 --> 00:04:05,160
而不是你儿子克利福德吗
and not your son Clifford?

133
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:07,210
他那天在餐馆加班
He was working late at the diner.

134
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:09,810
那是他出狱之后唯一能找到的工作
It was the only place he could get a job when he got out.

135
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:13,320
有两个人来抢劫餐馆
Two men came in to rob the place,

136
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,190
克利福德想要阻止他们
and when Clifford tried to stop them,

137
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,130
结果被枪杀了
he was shot and killed.

138
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:22,690
我深表遗憾
I'm so sorry.

139
00:04:24,610 --> 00:04:28,280
我这辈子含辛茹苦
I worked my whole life

140
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:30,000
供他上学
to put him through school

141
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:32,090
结果他却死在
and he ends up dying

142
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:35,250
那家破餐馆
in the back of that shit restaurant

143
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:37,330
死在那么个破地方
in that shit part of town.

144
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:40,190
你能告诉陪审团你今天为什么
Can you tell the jury why you agreed

145
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:42,270
愿意过来为我分享你的故事吗
to come share your story for me today?

146
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:45,490
监狱
Prison

147
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:48,430
毁了克利福德的一生
ruined Clifford's life...

148
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:54,390
如果你从一开始就是我们的律师的话
And if you had been our lawyer from day one,

149
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,850
他根本不会被判有罪
he never would have been convicted in the first place.

150
00:05:01,570 --> 00:05:02,960
谢谢你  格洛丽亚
Thank you, Gloria.

151
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:07,090
没有其他问题了  法官大人
No more questions, Your Honor.

152
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:14,580
丹纳女士
Mrs. Danner,

153
00:05:15,460 --> 00:05:18,410
我恰好很熟悉你儿子的案子
I happen to be familiar with your son's case.

154
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,530
我知道为了重审该案
And I understand that in order to reopen it,

155
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:25,340
罗斯先生冒了将他的刑期增加到无期的风险
Mr. Ross risked increasing his sentence to life.

156
00:05:25,710 --> 00:05:26,800
是这样的
That's correct.

157
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,570
我想知道如果他赌输了
Well, I'd like to know how you'd have felt

158
00:05:28,570 --> 00:05:30,030
你会是什么感觉
if he lost that gamble.

159
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,480
我会彻底绝望
I'd have been devastated.

160
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,520
如果真的是那样  而你又发现
And if that happened, how would you have felt

161
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,630
罗斯先生根本就不是个律师
if you then found out 

162
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:37,570
那你又会是什么感觉
that Mr. Ross wasn't even a lawyer after all?

163
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:38,530
反对  法官大人
Objection, Your Honor,

164
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:40,200
她可以问多少假设性的问题
how many hypotheticals can she ask?

165
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,260
没关系
That's okay.

166
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,230
我觉得这里的每个人都知道
I think everybody in this courtroom knows

167
00:05:44,230 --> 00:05:45,590
那会是什么感觉
how they would feel.

168
00:05:47,410 --> 00:05:49,090
我没有问题了  法官大人
No more questions, Your Honor.

169
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:53,480
我根本不会在乎那张纸
I wouldn't have cared what a piece of paper had to say,

170
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:57,980
因为罗斯先生是我唯一碰到
because Mr. Ross is the only lawyer I ever ran into

171
00:05:57,980 --> 00:06:00,600
愿意帮我儿子的律师
that ever gave a damn about my son.

172
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:07,180
罗斯先生  你还要传唤第二位证人吗
Mr. Ross, would you care to call your next witness?

173
00:06:11,470 --> 00:06:12,450
我想不到比这位
I can't imagine anyone

174
00:06:12,450 --> 00:06:14,170
更适合的证人了  法官大人
being more eloquent than that, Your Honor.

175
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:17,510
辩方没有证人了
Defense rests.

176
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:47,990
